                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d595">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/1271: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bliss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos Aires</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-07-05T21:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 5, 1931—9 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 6—12:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>76. Yesterday afternoon at the Embassy reception the President informed me that
                    Argentina had offered to Bolivia and Paraguay the despatch of a commission to
                    the Chaco to prevent possible conflicts between the armed forces of those
                    countries but that neither country had yet accepted. Although the President
                    stated that Argentina had not offered to arbitrate the fundamental question in
                    dispute, yet it <pb facs="0859" n="745" xml:id="pg_745"/> was quite evident that
                    he would accept an invitation to arbitrate if offered by both Bolivia and
                    Paraguay. It was my impression that the President would even offer to act as
                    arbitrator if he thought it possible to arrive at an acceptable solution.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bliss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
